                     /product="ankyrin-like protein"
                     /label=LSDV152
                     /note="ankyrin-like protein; similar to Vaccinia virus str
                     ain Copenhagen B4R; although the function of the ankyrin-l 
                     ike protein is not completely understood, it is highly con 
                     served throughout the Orthopoxvirus genus; it may be criti 
                     cal for overcoming cellular restriction factors; the ankyr 
                     in-like protein of the modified vaccinia virus ankara inte 
                     racts with Skp1a, a member of the Skp1a-Cullin-1-F-box (SC 
                     F) ubiquitin ligase complex; The poxviridae are enveloped 
                     unsegmented dsDNA viruses; unlike many dsDNA viruses that 
                     replicate in the host nucleus poxviruses encode their own 
                     replication machinery and therefore replicate in the cytop 
                     lasm; viral genes are expressed in a bi-phasic manner with 
                     early genes encoding non-structural proteins involved in 
                     genome replication and late genes encoding the viral struc 
                     tural proteins"
